        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): auto-recover orphaned running sessions in reaper sweep",
        "body": "## Summary\nSessions stuck in `status=\"running\"` after a gateway crash are now automatically recovered by the cron reaper. If a session hasn\\'t been updated for more than 2 hours, the reaper marks it as `\"done\"`.\n\n## Problem\nAfter a gateway crash or restart, cron run sessions remain stuck with `status=\"running\"` indefinitely. The reaper only pruned sessions based on retention age (24h default), not based on staleness.\n\n## Solution\nAdd orphan recovery logic to the reaper sweep:\n- Detection: Check all `cron:run` sessions with `status=\"running\"` and `updatedAt < now - 2 hours`\n- Recovery: Mark those sessions as `status=\"done\"` with `endedAt = updatedAt`\n- Timing: Recovery runs before retention-based prune, so UI reflects corrected status\n\n## Changes\n- `src/cron/session-reaper.ts` — +40 lines (orphan detection + recovery)\n- `src/cron/session-reaper.test.ts` — +38 lines (test coverage)\n\n## Test Plan\n- [x] 3h-old session with `status=\"running\"` → marked done ✅\n- [x] 30min-old session with `status=\"running\"` → stays running ✅\n- [x] Result reports `orphansRecovered=1, pruned=0` ✅\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n✅ Fully backward compatible — `ReaperResult.orphansRecovered` is additive\n\nSee detailed proposal: references/github-contribute/PR-1-CRON-SESSION-RECOVERY.md",
